=Sengzhao 僧肇=
chinese monk, 374-414
==Works==
* [[寶藏論]]
* [[肇論]]

==Literature and Translations==
===Monographs===
* Robert H. Sharf: Coming to Terms with Chinese Buddhism. A Reading of the Treasure Store Treatise. Honolulu: University of Hawaii Press, 2002.
* [[Walther Liebenthal]]:The book  of Chao: a translation from the  original Chinese with introduction, notes and appendicies. Peking: The Catholic University of  Peking, 1948
* Richard H. Robinson: Early Mādhyamika in India and China. Madison [u.a.] : Univ of Wisconsin Pr., 1967: 123-155, 210-232.
===Articles===
* Wing Tsit-chan: Seng-chao's Doctrine of Reality. In: A Source Book in Chinese Philosophy. New Jersey: Princeton University Press, 1963: 343-356. 
* Shohei Ichimura: ON THE PARADOXICAL METHOD OF THE CHINESE MAADHYAMIKA: SENG-CHAO AND THE CHAO-LUN TREATISE, Journal of Chinese Philosophy, Vol.19 (1992): 51-71. [[@http://ccbs.ntu.edu.tw/FULLTEXT/JR-JOCP/ichimura.htm|fulltext]] 
* Michael Berman: TIME AND EMPTINESS IN THE CHAO-LUN.  Journal of Chinese Philosophy, Vol.24 (1997): 43-58. [[@http://ccbs.ntu.edu.tw/FULLTEXT/JR-JOCP/muchael.htm|fulltext]]
* Sung-ja HAN: The Middle Path of No Abiding and No Leaving in the "Immutability of Things" by Seng-chao. International Journal of Buddhist Thought & Culture February 2004, Vol. 4, pp. 165~187. [[@http://ftp.buddhism.org/Publications/IABTC/Vol04_08_Sung-ja%20Han.pdf|pdf]] 
* Ming-Wood LIU: SENG-CHAO AND THE MAADHYAMIKA WAY OF REFUTATION, Journal of Chinese Philosophy, Vol. 14 (1987): 97-110 [[@http://ccbs.ntu.edu.tw/FULLTEXT/JR-JOCP/liu1.htm|fulltext]] 